WEBVTT

00:00.501 --> 00:02.662
<i>I am glad you crave
my best conjugations</i>

00:02.737 --> 00:04.398
<i>Previously on Smash...</i>

00:04.538 --> 00:06.369
<i>When you love
someone...</i>

00:06.440 --> 00:09.034
The Fringe? In two weeks?
That's completely insane.

00:09.410 --> 00:12.038
I usually don't like
a lot of people.

00:12.113 --> 00:13.512
Just don't let
me down, okay?

00:13.981 --> 00:16.006
Ladies and gentlemen,
Terry Falls.

00:16.082 --> 00:18.051
Ah, yes. Young Cecile.

00:18.119 --> 00:19.450
How you have grown.

00:19.520 --> 00:21.215
He's playing
the whole thing like
it's a comedy.

00:21.288 --> 00:22.755
I've decided
to go off my meds.

00:23.391 --> 00:26.588
Thanks for the files.
Eileen will never
work without me again.

00:26.660 --> 00:28.821
Have you got a brilliant
book for the read-through
this afternoon?

00:28.896 --> 00:31.421
I'm not going to produce it.
I have a version that I love.

00:31.499 --> 00:33.091
How did you get this?
He sent it to me.

00:33.167 --> 00:35.192
It was just the draft
I liked the most.

00:35.269 --> 00:37.794
We need a tie-breaker.
Since it's up to me...

00:41.976 --> 00:45.537
<i>Here she is,
Miss Marilyn Monroe</i>

00:45.946 --> 00:49.438
<i>Will she have the answers
that our readers want to know?</i>

00:49.517 --> 00:51.417
<i>From India
And Paris</i>

00:51.485 --> 00:53.248
<i>And from just
across the pond</i>

00:53.788 --> 00:59.886
<i>We have so many questions for
America's smart, dumb blonde</i>

00:59.960 --> 01:01.951
Okay, you lot,
go up stage left.

01:02.029 --> 01:03.621
You lot, go up
stage right.

01:03.964 --> 01:05.556
Because, oh,
look out,

01:05.633 --> 01:09.399
here comes the enormous,
expensive and totally
unnecessary plane

01:09.470 --> 01:11.734
that's about to
land on the stage.

01:11.806 --> 01:16.106
And the steps roll in,
and Karen walks down...

01:16.544 --> 01:18.034
It's gonna be great.
Spectacular.

01:18.112 --> 01:20.103
It's for tourists.
It isn't art.

01:20.681 --> 01:22.114
I completely disagree.

01:22.416 --> 01:26.682
It's a dynamic,
Technicolor fantasy of
the way Marilyn made herself.

01:27.121 --> 01:29.487
And it's going
to fit perfectly
in our new book.

01:29.557 --> 01:32.355
Your new book.
As opposed to
mine and Julia's,

01:32.426 --> 01:34.360
which I was
really looking
forward to directing.

01:34.428 --> 01:35.554
Best thing
I've ever written.

01:35.729 --> 01:37.356
We said we'd go with
whatever Eileen chose.

01:37.431 --> 01:41.492
Well, clearly I only said that
because I thought she would
make the right choice.

01:41.836 --> 01:44.236
And I did.
And I agree.

01:44.305 --> 01:47.297
Though we might
have to cut something
to make room for this number.

01:48.876 --> 01:49.934
There's a lot of music.

01:57.118 --> 01:58.881
Is this a theater
or a bar?

01:58.953 --> 02:01.012
I knew the last slot
meant the crappiest space.

02:01.088 --> 02:03.454
It's the Fringe.
You get two days
and a shoebox.

02:03.958 --> 02:05.823
Sometimes
it's a disaster.

02:05.893 --> 02:07.758
But sometimes
you break out.

02:08.294 --> 02:09.762
I like it.

02:10.097 --> 02:13.157
It's not too fancy,
which is good for us.

02:13.501 --> 02:17.562
It's got good acoustics,
'cause it's small.
And who cares anyway.

02:17.638 --> 02:19.071
The show's good.

02:19.306 --> 02:22.104
It better be.
We're on in 10 hours.

