36:58.948 --> 37:01.542
<i>Let the broken pieces</i>

37:01.884 --> 37:04.944
<i>Let the broken pieces</i>

37:05.487 --> 37:08.217
<i>Let the broken pieces</i>

37:28.578 --> 37:30.341
Tomorrow we go into tech.

37:30.413 --> 37:34.816
Now is the absolute
last moment to tweak
anything major.

37:35.018 --> 37:40.752
So I thought it would
be nice if we took the time
to say whatever it is we feel.

37:41.191 --> 37:42.215
Anything.

37:43.660 --> 37:44.684
Constructive,

37:45.528 --> 37:46.620
destructive...

37:46.696 --> 37:48.391
Anything at all.

37:51.001 --> 37:52.298
Fine.

37:52.569 --> 37:55.367
Fine. You don't have to
talk about each other.

37:56.606 --> 37:58.073
How about me?

37:58.174 --> 38:00.233
What do you think
of my performance?

38:06.883 --> 38:07.907
Anyone?

38:09.319 --> 38:12.482
You guys, he's asking
us to be honest.

38:12.822 --> 38:14.847
He means it.
He wants to hear the truth.

38:15.525 --> 38:17.425
This is our chance
to make it good.

38:17.794 --> 38:19.989
Just tell him how bad it is
and we can make it better.

38:20.297 --> 38:22.822
Please, tell me.

38:28.638 --> 38:29.696
It's dreadful.

38:29.773 --> 38:30.933
Appalling.

38:31.007 --> 38:33.532
I've never been
so embarrassed by
my work before.

38:33.610 --> 38:35.100
<i>And I was in
Urban Cowboy.</i>

38:35.211 --> 38:36.269
It's that bad.

38:36.346 --> 38:38.075
- It's really bad.
- It's just awful.

38:38.148 --> 38:40.582
Yeah, it's terrible.
Unbelievable.

38:40.650 --> 38:43.312
Is any of it any good?

38:44.220 --> 38:48.156
The text was.
The music is.
The cast is.

38:48.425 --> 38:50.325
You can be, too,
if you want to be.

38:51.695 --> 38:53.959
Do we still have time
to make some changes?

38:54.297 --> 38:55.696
Absolutely.

38:55.865 --> 38:56.854
Okay.

39:01.604 --> 39:03.731
Hey. You came.

39:04.140 --> 39:05.471
I did.

39:05.675 --> 39:07.267
It has real promise.

39:07.577 --> 39:08.703
So, you really quit, huh?

39:08.778 --> 39:10.040
It appears I did.

39:10.113 --> 39:12.206
You ruled!
She did.

39:13.049 --> 39:14.107
Thank you.

39:14.451 --> 39:16.817
Nice work.
You, too.

39:16.886 --> 39:19.946
I agree. You were wonderful.

39:20.490 --> 39:22.549
Where can I find
the writers?
They're right here.

39:22.625 --> 39:25.253
I'm Kyle, I did the book.
Jimmy wrote the music
and lyrics.

39:25.328 --> 39:28.729
Scott Nichols.
I'm the artistic director
at Manhattan Theater Workshop.

39:28.798 --> 39:30.698
Wow. And you came
to see our show?

39:30.800 --> 39:32.461
I'll admit I only
came because the show

39:32.535 --> 39:33.968
I had tickets
for got canceled,

39:34.037 --> 39:37.438
but I'm glad I did.
It's really intriguing.

39:37.507 --> 39:39.202
It's just the kind of
project that I look for.

39:39.576 --> 39:40.770
Who's the director?

39:40.844 --> 39:42.141
We don't have one.

39:42.746 --> 39:43.906
Yeah, you do.

39:44.781 --> 39:46.271
Derek?

39:46.349 --> 39:47.338
Hi, Scott.
How you doing?

39:47.417 --> 39:49.749
<i>What are you doing here?
Aren't you directing
Bombshell?</i>

39:49.819 --> 39:51.081
Not anymore, no.

39:51.755 --> 39:53.620
And you'd both be
on board to star?

39:54.557 --> 39:56.149
I'm not an actor.
Yes, he is.

39:57.060 --> 39:58.493
And what about you?

39:58.561 --> 40:00.825
<i>I can't.
I'm in Bombshell.</i>

40:00.897 --> 40:02.558
Oh, that's too bad.

40:03.600 --> 40:05.659
Would you all like
to go and have a drink
and talk about the show?

40:05.735 --> 40:07.362
God, yes.

40:09.906 --> 40:11.339
Where we going?

40:14.677 --> 40:16.110
Hey. You're coming, right?

40:16.713 --> 40:20.012
Hey, don't you have
to be at rehearsal
early tomorrow morning?

40:20.183 --> 40:22.845
Yeah. Well, have fun.

40:23.686 --> 40:25.654
Yeah, see you around.

40:41.571 --> 40:42.560
What's that?

40:43.106 --> 40:46.166
That's proof that Jerry
is a lying son of a bitch.

40:46.543 --> 40:50.445
It's a background
check on Nick Felder.
Ellis did it last year.

40:51.314 --> 40:52.838
I found it in Jerry's office.

40:53.249 --> 40:54.910
Wait, what does
that mean?

40:54.984 --> 40:58.681
It means that Jerry
was paying Ellis
for information

40:58.755 --> 41:02.350
so he could shut down the show
and take it over himself.

41:02.425 --> 41:03.790
Mission accomplished.

41:04.360 --> 41:05.657
Oh, my God.

41:07.163 --> 41:08.528
Have you talked to him?

41:08.965 --> 41:11.934
No, and I'm not going to
until I get the show back.

41:12.001 --> 41:13.866
Then I'll kill him
if he's lucky.

41:15.605 --> 41:17.129
What do we do
until then?

41:17.807 --> 41:20.241
Even if we got a new
director tomorrow,

41:20.310 --> 41:22.505
he or she would
need weeks of prep.

41:23.480 --> 41:25.243
What if he were
already prepped?

41:25.315 --> 41:26.304
What do you mean?

41:26.382 --> 41:27.872
We have a director.

41:32.222 --> 41:33.246
Oh, my God.

41:34.457 --> 41:39.485
We have a director.
Tom, we have a director!

41:41.297 --> 41:43.060
Who?
You!

41:43.733 --> 41:45.496
You know this show
better than anyone.

41:45.568 --> 41:48.867
You know the cast,
the costumes,
the choreography,

41:48.938 --> 41:52.237
sometimes he does it
around the apartment when
he thinks no one's looking.

41:52.308 --> 41:55.038
Look what you did
today in rehearsal.

41:55.345 --> 41:58.075
You've got the vision, Tom.
You see the show.

41:58.581 --> 42:00.310
Like Derek used to.

42:00.550 --> 42:04.042
Even better.
'Cause you see it the way
we want it to be.

42:04.654 --> 42:08.385
I will be with you
every step of the way.

42:08.725 --> 42:10.283
What do you say?

42:11.227 --> 42:12.888
<i>You want to save
Bombshell, or what?</i>

42:21.905 --> 42:23.270
I thought you'd never ask.

